ism of Indiana’s Dominican Spanish in language that propels the book forward with the relentless beat of a merengue, Papi is furious, musical, and full of wit—a passionate, overwhelming, and very human explosion of artistic virtuosity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aOrganized crimevFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  asanto domingo, wealth, poverty, race, ethnicity, divorce, childhood, fathers and daughters, isolation, abandonment, belonging, family, drug dealer, danger, crime, criminals, latino, hispanic, puerto rico, horror, science fiction, machismo, violence, literature, women authors, diversity, multiculturalism, people of color, translated works, translation, satire, social commentary.1 aObejas, Achy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311071098440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226244921423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226244921/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles